Author:  BOWEN
Vol / Page:  14
Edition:
Quote:  If sheep's grease, being slightly poisonous, enters the pores of the skin, grease boils and skin troubles arise. The shearer, however, may contract grease boils, rheumatics and chills through shearing wet sheep.
